I've been learning about day trading for a few weeks now and I have a few questions: 
 
Since day traders are supposed to close their positions EVERY day, wouldn't the price of the stock go down at the end of each day with the amount of traders closing their positions? 
 
And, is "closing your position" the same as selling your position at the end of the day? 
 
Say I purchased $AAPL for $100 in the morning, and it closes at $105, and since I'm "closing" my position (or selling it?) wouldn't that cause the price to drop a bit? 
 
Or you sell your position when you're ready to take profit, so the timing doesn't matter too much? I hope this makes sense, thanks!!
